                <h1>The History and Popularity of Pepperoni</h1>
                <p>Pepperoni, a popular pizza topping, has an interesting background that dates back to Italian-American cuisine. Originating from southern Italy, this cured meat is made from a blend of pork and beef, seasoned with spices like paprika and fennel. Its smoky flavor and appealing red color contribute to its widespread popularity across the globe.</p>
